  "prompt": "I'm 21 years old and I want to become a politician. What should I do?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to help you pursue a career in politics:\n\n1. Educational preparation\n- Study political science, public policy, or a related field\n- Consider getting a master's degree in public administration or policy\n\n2. Gain political experience\n- Volunteer for political campaigns\n- Join local political party organizations\n- Participate in student government\n- Intern with politicians or government offices\n\n3. Network\n- Attend political events\n- Connect with local politicians and activists\n- Join political organizations and clubs\n\n4. Develop key skills\n- Public speaking\n- Communication\n- Critical thinking\n- Leadership\n- Understanding of policy issues\n\n5. Start local\n- Run for local office like city council or school board\n- Build a reputation in your community\n- Gain grassroots support\n\n6. Stay informed\n- Follow current events\n- Understand local and national political issues\n- Read political news and analysis\n\n7. Build a professional image\n- Create a strong social media presence\n- Develop a clear political platform\n- Be authentic and passionate\n\n8. Consider additional steps\n- Law school\n- Campaign management experience\n- Working for non-profit organizations\n\nRemember, political careers take time, persistence, and dedication to build.",
